\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 197}, {\"ngram\": \"61 games\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A'ja Wilson scored a game-high 21 points for the Americans who won the title for the 10th time overall, surviving a buzzer-beating shot from France's Gabby Williams.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"A'ja Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabby Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a game-high 21 points\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 252}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 257, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"the title\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 288}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10th time\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 306}, {\"ngram\": \"a buzzer-beating shot\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hosts needed a three to force overtime in Paris but Williams' foot was on the three-point line as she let go of the ball, so her shot counted for just two points in a dramatic finale.\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 425, \"end\": 430,